  "issue_title": "feature: add local screen summary and suggested actions",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #38\n\n## Problem\n\nTouchPilot needs a visible local AI feature from screen context: it should be able to summarize the current screen and suggest useful actions without cloud inference.\n\nThis should start deterministic and context-driven. A local model hook can be added later, but Milestone 3 should not depend on a VLM or cloud model.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd local screen summary and suggested action generation from `ScreenContext`:\n\n```text\nScreenContext\n  -> screen summary\n  -> suggested actions\n  -> agent/UI event output\n```\n\nExample output:\n\n```text\nI see the Settings screen. Visible actions include Network & internet, Connected devices, Apps, Notifications, and Battery. I can open one of these sections, scroll, or go back.\n```\n\nSuggested actions should map to existing safe tool concepts where possible:\n\n- tap visible item\n- type into visible input\n- scroll\n- go back\n- open app-specific visible section\n\n## User workflow\n\nUser asks:\n\n- `What screen am I on?`\n- `What can you do here?`\n- `What buttons are visible?`\n- `Suggest actions for this screen`\n\nTouchPilot replies locally using the current screen context.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis makes TouchPilot feel like a real local AI assistant while still using deterministic, inspectable local logic first.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\n- Summaries should avoid exposing sensitive details from password fields, private messages, tokens, or account screens.\n- Suggested actions are not execution approval. Any selected action must still go through validation and policy.\n- Suggestions should be conservative on sensitive screens.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add local screen summary generation from screen context.\n- [ ] Add suggested action generation from visible controls.\n- [ ] Suggested actions reference existing tool concepts without executing automatically.\n- [ ] UI or agent event path can display the summary and suggestions.\n- [ ] Sensitive text is redacted or avoided in summaries where practical.\n- [ ] Tests cover Settings-like screen, launcher-like screen, input-field screen, and empty/weak context.\n- [ ] No cloud model/backend is required.\n\n## References\n\n- Parent issue: #38\n- Depends on: screen context model and builder issues\n- `docs/ROADMAP.md` Milestone 3\n",
